President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed shock and grief over the death of Eunice Ndanusa-Isaiah, the mother of the LEADERSHIP Newspapers founder and publisher, late Sam Nda-Isaiah, who died in December 2020. Reacting to the news of her demise, President Buhari in a statement by presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu, on Sunday, said: “The passing of Eunice Ndanusa Isaiah is particularly painful in view of the fact that it comes one year after the death of her first son, Mr. Sam Nda-Isaiah.” According to the President, “losing a prominent son and his mother within the space of one year is a difficult thing to bear for a family. “As you grieve over this devastating death of a great mother, I send you my deepest sympathies at this difficult and trying moment. “May her gentle soul rest in peace,” the President added.